Detailed Description

Convenience class for building necessary data used in the Millikan-White vibration-translation energy relaxation model.

MillikanWhiteModelData ( const class Thermodynamics::Thermodynamics &  thermo,
size_t  index,
double  thetav 
)

Constructs default data for Millikan-White model from thermo model, species index, and characteristic vibrational temperature.

Default values for the A and B parameters in the Millikan-White model are taken from the original formulas in the paper:

\begin{align*} &A_{ij} = 1.16e-3 \mu_{ij}^{1/2} \theta_{i}^{4/3} \\ &B_{ij} = 0.015 \mu_{ij}^{1/4} \end{align*}

where \(\mu_{ij}\) is the reduced mass of the vibrator and colliding partner in g/mol, and \(\theta_{i}\) is the characteristic vibrational temperature of the vibrator. The default value for Park's reference cross section is taken as 10^-16 cm^2, based on recommendation in [1]. The high-temperature limiting cross section is based on [4].
